events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had a game-high 30 points, Tim Hardaway Jr. chipped in 28 points against his former team, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the New York Knicks 121-100 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs' Doncic, Hardaway team up in 121-100 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored 24 points on 10-of-11 shooting and the Sacramento Kings handed the undermanned Los Angeles Clippers their worst loss of the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis scores 24, leads Kings' 123-96 rout of Clippers

headlines.description: — Bobby Portis scored 20 points and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Charlotte Hornets 105-96 on Saturday night, despite missing star forward Giannis Antetokounmpo.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis-less Bucks cruise to 105-96 win over Hornets

headlines.description: — O.G. Anunoby matched his season high with 32 points, Pascal Siakam had 26 points and 10 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors beat short-handed Orlando 121-108 Saturday, handing the slumping Magic their eighth consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby matches season high 32, Raptors rout Magic 121-108

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 33 points in his return to action and the Oklahoma City Thunder took advantage of Rudy Gobert's early ejection to post a chippy 135-128 win over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Thunder post physical win over T-Wolves

events.name: Houston Rockets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins shoots more than 100 3-pointers most practices, as many reps as needed “until I feel good.”
headlines.shortLinkText: Andrew Wiggins scores 36 points, leads Warriors past Rockets

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored a career-high 45 points and blocked a potential 3-pointer with 4.6 seconds left to lead the Portland Trail Blazers to a 116-111 win over the Utah Jazz on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons' career-best 45 points carries Portland past Utah
